author: Chloe Chomicki
title: Dengue cases in Townsville could potentially be ruled an outbreak after local cases confirmed
description: As north Queensland health authorities grapple with rising COVID-19 figures there's been a resurgence in local dengue and Ross River fever cases.
content:
Posted 
March 27, 2020 13:33:24
The Townsville Hospital and Health Service says it may declare an outbreak of dengue fever in the city with two confirmed cases and another suspected.
